f-century leading up to the French invasions of 1790s. As the state’s power continued to rise during this second time span, the Church was often humbled and the tribunal’s activity was much reduced. Enriched by stories drawn from the files, which often allowed the accused to speak in their own voices, Punishment and Penance provides a window into the workings of a tribunal in this period.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aEcclesiastical courtszItalyzNovaraxHistory. 0aPenancexHistoryzItalyzNovara. 0aPunishmentzItalyzNovaraxHistory. 0aTrials (Blasphemy)zItalyzNovaraxHistory. 4aDISCOUNT-B. 7aRELIGION / History.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978144266052640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781442660526423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781442660526.jpg  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK